1
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,360
(CRASHING)

2
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:19,680
-(MAN GROANING)
-(SLEIGH BELLS JINGLING)

3
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:21,240
SANTA: Moron!

4
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:23,480
Numbskull!

5
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,320
-ELf!
-IAN: That's racist.

6
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:29,040
SANTA: Of course it's not racist.
You are an elf.

7
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,160
SANTA: Chimneys?
IAN: I'm sorry.

8
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:35,680
SANTA: I'm just checking that
you can see these massive chimneys.

9
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:37,760
IAN: (STAMMERS) They're hard to miss.

10
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:40,560
SANTA: Well, as you've clearly
demonstrated, Ian.

11
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:42,920
-(SIREN WAILING)
-Donner! Donner and Blitzen!

12
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:44,560
Come on down here, boys.

13
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:47,040
Good boys, good boys. Good...

14
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,520
-Rudolph!
-(REINDEERS BELLOWING)

15
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:52,600
SANTA: Just clear all the tangerines up.
Pick 'em up, all of them, Ian.

16
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:55,360
IAN: You know no one really
likes your tangerines, don't you?

17
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:56,840
How dare you!

18
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,960
That's my signature gift.
That and the walnut.

19
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:02,640
IAN: Down here, boys, come on.
Come... Rudolph!

20
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:10,160
Uh... Sir, we've been seen.

21
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,440
-Hello!
-Hello.

22
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:15,880
IAN: Hello. (LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

23
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,920
Hello... Human.

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,720
You can't call her human.

25
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,520
It's not racist, they don't mind.

26
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,080
Oh, shut up, both of you.

27
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:28,880
Oh, sorry about this... Girl.

28
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:33,760
We... We are just three passing

29
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:37,440
perfectly ordinary roof people

30
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:40,920
doing some emergency roof things.

31
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,880
Carry on. Merry Christmas.

32
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:48,040
If it is Christmas. I mean... (LAUGHS)

33
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:52,240
I don't much care for things
like that myself. (SCOFFS)

34
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:55,560
I mean, Christmas. (LAUGHING)

35
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:59,560
Are you... Santa Claus?

36
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:02,520
Me? Me. No!

37
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,400
Oh, no.

38
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,520
No, it's ridiculous. (LAUGHS)

39
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,040
-No, no, no.
-(BELLS JINGLING)

40
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:14,680
WOLF: Rudolph! Rudolph! Down here now!

41
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:18,600
All right, fine, yes, yes, it's me.

42
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,280
(CHUCKLES) Guilty.

43
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,400
How did you recognise me?

44
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:27,000
You know how you grew the beard
as a bit of a disguise?

45
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,400
People have picked up on it.

46
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:32,200
Okay, no, hang on, stop, shut up.

47
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:36,800
What? Seriously?
You... You're Father Christmas?

48
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:39,040
-You're real?
-Of course I'm real.

49
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,560
-Ho-ho-ho!
-How could he not be real?

50
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:43,800
Huh? How do you think those presents
got under the tree every year?

51
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,160
By magic?

52
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:48,200
-Well, I thought it was my mum and dad.
-Mum and Dad.

53
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,840
(LAUGHING)

54
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,560
(SARCASTICALLY) Well, of course it was!

55
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,200
I mean, it makes perfect sense.

56
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,120
Yeah, your mum and dad,

57
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:58,240
one day a year, for no particular
reason, just out of the blue,

58
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:01,160
suddenly decide to give you
a great big pile of presents.

59
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:04,120
No, no, no.
Because they love you so much.

60
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,640
It's a lovely story, dear.

61
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,640
Yeah, but it's time to start living
in the real world, yeah?

62
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:13,800
Okay, right, Clara Oswald.

63
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:16,400
Mostly favours
travel books, science kits.

64
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,960
Strict ban on hair products,
marginal for the naughty list, '93.

65
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:22,480
(TUTTING)
Believer until the age of nine.

66
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,800
Why did you stop?

67
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,840
Because you're a fairy tale.

68
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,280
I grew out of fairy tales.

69
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,800
(SANTA SIGHING)

70
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:34,200
Did you, Clara? Did you really?

71
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:37,320
(WHOOSHING)

72
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,680
Clara, I want you to step
inside the Tardis.

73
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:47,320
I don't want you to talk,
I want you to do as I ask, please.

74
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,800
That was good, with the box.

75
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:51,760
Hmm. Not often we get upstaged
on a rooftop.

76
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:55,800
(SOFTLY) Yes, I'm really here, I'm back.

77
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,080
Now get inside the Tardis.

78
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,720
I know what this is.

79
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:12,080
I know what's happening,
and I know what's at stake.

80
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,920
I don't think you do, Doctor.

81
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,680
But I promise,
before this Christmas Day is done,

82
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,200
you'll be glad of my help.

83
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,800
Happy Easter.

84
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:24,320
-Brutal.
-Cool exit line, though.

85
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,960
Be sure to save some room
for a tangerine, Doctor.

86
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,120
Nobody likes tangerines.

87
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:38,240
I'm really back here.
This is... This is real, yeah?

88
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,000
Doctor? Talk to me.

89
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,240
I never thought
I was gonna see you again.

90
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,760
What is going on out there?
What's happening?

91
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,880
(WHOOSHING)

92
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:58,200
Oh, that noise.
Never knew how much I loved it.

93
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,760
There's something you have to
ask yourself, and it's important.

94
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:07,800
Your life may depend on it.
Everybody's life.

95
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,120
Do you really believe in Santa Claus?

96
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,800
Do you know what?

97
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,400
Yeah.

98
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:23,480
Right now, yeah, I think I do.

99
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,280
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

100
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,760
(WIND BLOWING)

101
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:17,200
ASHLEY: You're now 20 feet
from the infirmary.

102
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:19,600
In a moment, as soon as you're ready,

103
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,320
I will disable the security protocols.

104
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:25,240
BELLOWS: Your neural link
is good and holding.

105
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:29,560
We stand ready to abort and extract
at the first sign of an anomaly.

106
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:32,960
We're going to be with you
every step of the way, Shona.

107
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:37,000
We're all depending on you
and we know you won't let us down.

108
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,120
Shona, I'm opening the door.

109
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,760
(BEEPS)

110
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,480
I need the toilet.

111
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:56,960
No, you don't.
We're monitoring your bodily functions.

112
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,120
SHONA: And how are you monitoring that?

113
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,720
That's rude. That is perverted.

114
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,880
Do you remember my briefing, Shona?

115
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:10,640
Yeah. No. I remember some of it.

116
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,040
-Some of it?
-How much?

117
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,240
Till he put his hand on my knee.

118
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:17,440
And then I was just grossing.

119
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,840
It was intended as a comfort.

120
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,440
For whom?

121
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,880
SHONA: All I could see was his nose,

122
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,840
with all the little hairs
coming out of It.

123
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,280
Have you seen those?

124
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,680
It's like he's got insects
trapped up there,

125
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,120
all trying to escape
with their wee wiggly legs.

126
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,920
Okay. Let's just go through this again.

127
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:38,440
There are four sleepers
inside the infirmary.

128
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:41,280
You're fine so long
as they don't wake up.

129
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,480
BELLOWS: She's in range.

130
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,800
Shona, I'm unsealing the infirmary.

131
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:48,520
From now on,
everything you think and feel,

132
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,960
everything you see,
will be available to them.

133
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:54,040
Most of it's fine, like traffic noise
when you're sleeping,

134
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:56,560
so long as you don't think about them,

135
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,960
so long as you don't look at them.

136
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:02,280
So don't think about them,
don't look at them.

137
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,840
(LIFE SUPPORT MACHINES BEEPING)

138
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,440
I thought there was going to be music.

139
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,560
We've got your playlist ready to go.

140
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:18,560
Focus on the words of the song,
try to remember what comes next.

141
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:22,000
-That will work like interference.
-BELLOWS: Here comes your earworm.

142
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,680
(BEEPS)

143
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:26,720
(MERRY XMAS EVERYBODY
BY SLADE PLAYING)

144
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,200
Keep your eyes on the floor.

145
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,760
Shut them where possible.

146
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:36,280
Focus on the music and move forward
through the infirmary.

147
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,840
(MERRY XMAS EVERYBODY
CONTINUES)

148
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,040
(HUMMING)

149
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:59,680
-Oh, dear Lord, she's not actually...
-If dancing works, it works.

150
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:01,280
This is insane.

151
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,840
This is working.

152
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,760
(VOCALISING)

153
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,120
(SCREAMING)

154
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,400
Shona? Shona, what's wrong?

155
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,440
-We've got ghosts!
-ASHLEY: Ghosts?

156
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:44,000
Yeah, yeah, there's a skeleton man
and a girl in a nightie.

157
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,840
(DOOR SHUTS)

158
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,000
CLARA: Doctor?

159
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,320
SHONA: No, no,
you're making me think about them!

160
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,040
Don't make me think about them!

161
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,520
What are they?

162
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,720
SHONA: Look, just don't ask,
yeah, and don't look.

163
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,640
Just don't make me think about them.

164
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,680
DOCTOR: Deaf.

165
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,880
Blind.

166
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,760
How can they see us?
How do they even know that we are here?

167
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:11,280
They can only see you, yeah,
if you see them.

168
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,640
So just don't look,
just don't even think about them.

169
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,000
Oh, telepathic.

170
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:18,560
They can home in on their own image
in someone else's brain.

171
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:21,560
Third-party perception, mind piracy.

172
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,600
-We're being hacked.
-What does that even mean?

173
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,560
DOCTOR: The visual input
from your optic nerve

174
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,440
is being streamed to their brains.

175
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,600
Stop broadcasting. Close your eyes.

176
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,680
(WHIMPERS)

177
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:46,840
They're still coming, aren't they?

178
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,240
It's because you're still
thinking about them.

179
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,280
So long as you retain them
as an active memory,

180
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,440
they can still home in.

181
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,560
-Think about something else.
-How?

182
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:56,360
# So here it is, Merry Christmas... #

183
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,520
Why is she singing?

184
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:01,760
She's running interference.
She's trying to distract herself.

185
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:05,520
-304 minus 17.
-Sorry, what?

186
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,160
-Plus 20, just do it.
-507.

187
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,920
-Minus 14 times 4.
-1972.

188
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,080
-Stop being so good at arithmetic!
-I can't help it!

189
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,360
Danny Pink!
What is Danny Pink up to right now?

190
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,120
He's probably flirting
with your neighbour.

191
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,080
Or texting women of low moral character.

192
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,360
(GASPS)

193
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,920
(STEADY BEEPING)

194
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:34,160
Don't you dare. Don't you dare say that.

195
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:36,320
-I was only...
-Danny Pink is dead.

196
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,400
-No, he's not.
-He's dead.

197
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:42,920
(DOOR OPENING)

198
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,040
Go, run, now, now, now!

199
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,480
Come on, quick, quick, quick, come on.

200
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,080
Here they come!

201
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,280
(HISSING)

202
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,600
(ALL SCREAMING)

203
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,480
(YELLS)

204
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:37,320
SANTA: Whoa!

205
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,440
-(BELLS JINGLING)
-Attaboy.

206
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,480
Well, now.

207
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:49,360
What seems to be the problem?

208
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:53,080
This is the North Pole,
we don't want any trouble here.

209
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,280
-(RUDOLPH MOOING)
-Hey, Rudolph.

210
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,440
-(BEEPS)
-Easy, son.

211
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,200
Oi, sleepyheads.

212
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,120
It's Christmas Eve, early to bed.

213
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:16,800
Who the hell are you?

214
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,520
Oh, take a guess, go on.
Push the boat out.

215
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,000
Tooth fairy maybe? The Easter bunny?

216
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:27,000
Shut your mouth, wise guy,
or you get yours.

217
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:29,920
-It's a balloon animal.
-That's a toy gun.

218
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,800
Yeah, but at least it's unsuitable
for children under four.

219
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:36,400
"Parts small enough to swallow,"”
so watch out.

220
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,520
(SIGHS)

221
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,000
Now, this is ridiculous.
Am I... Am I dreaming?

222
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,600
Oh, very good.

223
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:44,760
I need to know exactly who you are
and what's happening here.

224
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:48,800
Hello, Ashley.
Lead scientist on a polar expedition.

225
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:51,200
(GASPS) That microscope
really paid off, didn't it?

226
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:54,000
Now, your mum and dad
wanted me to get you a toy one,

227
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:56,280
but sometimes, I take a chance.

228
00:13:56,560 --> 00:14:00,200
Who are you?
Why are you dressed like that?

229
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:02,160
What do you think?

230
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:05,760
Come on, this is mental.
This is totally not happening.

231
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:09,840
I got three words, Shona.
Don't make me use 'em.

232
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,320
What three words?

233
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:13,440
My Little Pony.

234
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,720
-Shut up, you.
-Yeah? I've got lots more, babe.

235
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,360
I will mark you, Santa.

236
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:21,160
Okay, Doctor, are you
going to explain what is going on?

237
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:24,560
-It's an invasion, Miss Oswald.
-An invasion of what?

238
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,000
-Elves?
-Whoa!

239
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,880
-That is racist.
-Elf ist.

240
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:31,920
Yeah, which is a bit hypocritical
from someone of your height.

241
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,840
Ah, you've seen them before, Doctor?

242
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,400
-I've heard of them.
-The Kantrofarri.

243
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:45,320
Colloquially known as the dream crabs.

244
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,560
Yeah, depending on how many of those
are already on Earth,

245
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,600
the human race may well
have seen its last day.

246
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:54,520
So are we going to stand about
arguing whether I'm real or not,

247
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:57,440
or are we gonna get busy
saving Christmas?

248
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:00,000
(GASPS) Santa goes badass.

249
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:02,360
-Oh, he's giving me the feels.
-Shut up.

250
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:05,160
That's a verbal warning, please stop it.

251
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,400
Is it dead?

252
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,880
I don't know. Possibly.

253
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:20,280
-I'm assuming extraterrestrial?
-Oh, definitely.

254
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,240
Then how can you
have heard of these things?

255
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,360
Guess.

256
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,760
Because you're extraterrestrial, too.

257
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,280
DOCTOR: Do you believe that?

258
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:31,400
-If you are Santa...
-Mmm-hmm.

259
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,200
...what are you doing here?

260
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,800
It's the North Pole. And I own it.

261
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,560
He means the actual pole.

262
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:39,480
It goes right through
the middle of the workshop.

263
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:43,160
-IAN: I've got a selfie with it.
-Show her. Look at Ian.

264
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,640
The North Pole isn't an actual pole.

265
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:47,040
Of course it is. Look.

266
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,200
If it was an actual pole,
it would not be stripey.

267
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:50,480
It's got to be stripey.

268
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:52,320
Otherwise you couldn't
see it moving around.

269
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:55,200
-Hmm.
-It's actually basic physics.

270
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:57,760
ASHLEY: Why's it called
a dream crab for a start?

271
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:58,880
DOCTOR: Theorise.

272
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:01,000
Because it generates a telepathic field.

273
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,920
-And...
-Alters perception...

274
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,600
-Meaning?
-I seem to be doing all the work here.

275
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,880
Meaning, we can't trust
anything that we see or hear.

276
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,160
-Go to the window.
-Why?

277
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:13,080
Because it gets worse.

278
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,680
ASHLEY: What is that?

279
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,480
DOCTOR: That's how Clara and I got here.

280
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:23,000
-ASHLEY: In a box?
-Technically, in a telephone kiosk.

281
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:26,000
(LAUGHS) How?

282
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,440
Because it's a spaceship in disguise.

283
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:32,640
Do you know what the big problem is
in telling fantasy and reality apart?

284
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,080
-ASHLEY: What?
-They're both ridiculous.

285
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,240
It's Christmas Eve.

286
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,320
Yeah. (SCOFFS)
You don't have to tell me that.

287
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,240
Yeah, well then, why aren't you
out delivering presents?

288
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,440
Technically, I am.

289
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,000
Well, you're not,
'cause you're stood right there.

290
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,840
Oh, Shona, grow up, love.

291
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,720
Yeah, do the math, baby.

292
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,040
There's not just one Santa
delivery team, how could there be?

293
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:52,800
There are 526,403,012 children

294
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:55,000
all expecting presents
before tomorrow morning.

295
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:57,560
So that's 22 million children per hour.

296
00:16:57,880 --> 00:17:00,240
That's impossible.
Obviously, I got a second sledge.

297
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,560
So we don't know
what is real and what isn't?

298
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,680
Exactly.

299
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:05,600
Are we in danger?

300
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:07,600
Oh, we're well past danger, Clara.

301
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:11,240
If I'm right and I usually am,
we're dying.

302
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:13,520
Then how do we stay alive?

303
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:16,120
I like you. Straight to the point.

304
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,560
I want you to show me how you
first encountered those creatures

305
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,280
and what happened to those
people in the infirmary.

306
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:23,400
I notice you all wear mini-cams.
So I assume that there is footage.

307
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:26,280
Is it possible I'm about to work
with someone who might be a dream?

308
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:27,560
If it helps, so am I.

309
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,880
(CHUCKLES)

310
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,720
We have footage on the drives.
I'll see what I can pull up.

311
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,520
Ashley.

312
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:36,200
What's this polar base for?
Why are you all here?

313
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,520
It's a long story.

314
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:45,160
What you said about Danny...

315
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:49,800
Unacceptable.

316
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:53,240
I know. I had to flood
your mind with random emotion.

317
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:54,520
Random?

318
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,080
You never told me he was dead.

319
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,640
You said he made it back.

320
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:00,920
I lied.

321
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:05,480
I lied so you'd go home to Gallifrey,
instead of fussing about me.

322
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,240
I never found Gallifrey.

323
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:10,480
I lied so you'd stay with Danny.

324
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:28,400
So we're dying then?

325
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,080
-Yes.
-CLARA: Why?

326
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,680
Oh, complicated.

327
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:33,680
How long do we have?

328
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:35,080
-No idea.
-Just...

329
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,080
Doctor, give me something to do.

330
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:38,360
Trust nothing.

331
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,240
Accept nothing you see.

332
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:42,800
Whatever happens,
interrogate everything.

333
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:45,680
-In case it's a lie.
-In case it's a lie.

334
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,400
Reindeer can't fly. They just can't.

335
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:55,800
No. No, they can't,
it's a scientific impossibility.

336
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:58,160
That is why I feed mine magic carrots.

337
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,720
-You all right?
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

338
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:08,960
I'm trying to talk sense
into beardy-weirdy.

339
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:10,400
You don't seem much like a scientist.

340
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,680
Well, that's a bit rude,
coming from a magician.

341
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,760
Why are you out here?
What brought you to the North Pole?

342
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,720
Long story, isn't it?

343
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:21,480
-You missed a killer question.
-Sorry, what?

344
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,200
-Beardy-weirdy...
-Yeah.

345
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:25,600
How do you get
all the presents in the sleigh?

346
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,720
-It's bigger on the inside.
-Ooh!

347
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,560
Doctor.

348
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,760
Sorry, starving.

349
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:43,320
-What am I looking at?
-BELLOWS: Footage from a week ago.

350
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,200
A side-expedition from our main mission.

351
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,200
What is your main mission?

352
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,840
Long story.

353
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,600
Ice cave directly beneath this base.

354
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:54,680
Now, look at what we found.

355
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:58,960
Dormant at first.

356
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,040
Until you looked at them too long.
Till you thought about them.

357
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,400
Exactly.

358
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:06,840
Sleeping, probably been
down there for centuries.

359
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,720
And it wakes up when you think about it?

360
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,040
They can detect their own
mental picture in any nearby mind.

361
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,400
That's Bellows' theory.

362
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:20,240
It's like it responds to the presence
of any data concerning itself.

363
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:21,400
Well, that was always the legend.

364
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:24,160
You think about a dream crab,
a dream crab is coming for you.

365
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,480
-(GLASS SHATTERS)
-This is where it gets really nasty.

366
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,000
Only now?

367
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,360
Okay, then what?

368
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:47,240
Little bit like facehuggers,
aren't they?

369
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:51,560
Facehuggers?

370
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:53,440
You know, Alien.

371
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,440
The horror movie, Alien.

372
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,720
There's a horror movie called Alien?

373
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:02,560
That's really offensive.
No wonder everyone keeps invading you.

374
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,920
BELLOWS: At first they just slept.

375
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:07,160
Couple of days, just lying there.

376
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:10,480
DOCTOR: And then they became aggressive?

377
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,240
If we got close enough, yeah.

378
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:15,200
It would take the dream crab
a little while to take control.

379
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,800
It depends how much
of the host brain was...

380
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,960
ASHLEY: Was what?

381
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,840
Digested.

382
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:26,840
Are they still alive under those things?

383
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,080
Depends what you call alive.

384
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:30,680
-Are they suffering?
-No, no, no, no.

385
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:33,800
The dream crab induces a dream state.

386
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:36,440
Keeps you happy and relaxed

387
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:39,800
in a perfectly realised dream world
as you dissolve.

388
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:43,960
Merciful, I suppose.

389
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,600
Compared to what?

390
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,400
Compared to that
turkey leg you keep eating.

391
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:51,200
Could you rewind for me?
I'd like to see them dormant again.

392
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:53,120
Clara, could you fetch me the dead one?

393
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:55,080
Maybe I could fetch you
a cup of tea while I'm at it?

394
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:58,720
Ooh, yes. And a punch in the face, too.

395
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:00,960
-My very next suggestion.
-Fair enough.

396
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,320
Doctor!

397
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,880
(GASPS)

398
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,560
-What's wrong?
-We're thinking about it.

399
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,760
Clara!

400
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:47,640
(WHISPERING) 100 minus 42 is 58 times 3
is 174 minus 32 is 142

401
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:50,600
divided by 7 is 20
(STAMMERS) and a bit...

402
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:54,560
Think about something else,
think about something else.

403
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:57,440
Danny Pink, Danny, Danny.

404
00:22:57,520 --> 00:23:00,400
Danny Pink, I love you
and I'll never see you again,

405
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:03,080
and I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
I lied, I'm sorry.

406
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,720
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

407
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,400
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry...

408
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,400
(SCREAMING)

409
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,720
(FOOTSTEPS)

410
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:25,640
Ho-ho-ho.

411
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:28,440
Who are you?

412
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:31,160
What do you mean, who am I?
Who do you think I am?

413
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:33,280
Danny.

414
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:34,560
Merry Christmas.

415
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,000
Come on.

416
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:39,000
-Come on where?
-Downstairs.

417
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,240
Why?

418
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,200
Well, you know what day it is?

419
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:46,400
What day is it?

420
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:49,720
Easter. It's Easter Day.

421
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,720
That's why I'm dressed like this,
I'm Father Easter.

422
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:54,760
Is that a thing?

423
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:57,000
(LAUGHING) No, because it's Christmas!

424
00:23:57,080 --> 00:24:00,560
Oh! You've made me want chocolate now.

425
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,240
Good, come on, you.

426
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:05,840
Out of bed, downstairs.
I have surprises.

427
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:08,120
Tickets for the Indian Orient Express,

428
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:11,680
that painting we saw in Paris,
and permission to own a cat.

429
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,120
How did you know?

430
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,240
Because those are exactly
the things I want

431
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:17,320
and you are too clever ever to be wrong.

432
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:20,920
Um, how do you make you clever
into me being clever?

433
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:22,440
I always protect your ego
from the truth.

434
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,000
Oh, um, thank you for that.

435
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,920
-It's Christmas.
-Hurry up then.

436
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:43,920
Danny?

437
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:49,120
Whose blackboard is that?

438
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,120
What blackboard?

439
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:56,560
Are you coming?

440
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,440
Yeah, just a moment.

441
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,840
Clara.

442
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:07,600
Coming.

443
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:24,640
Clara.

444
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:27,440
Yeah.

445
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:31,160
Just a minute.

446
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:05,320
DOCTOR (DISTORTED):
Clara! Clara!

447
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:09,880
Clara!

448
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:15,960
(SIGHS)

449
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,640
DANNY: Well, come on then.

450
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:28,000
You don't know what I'm wearing
underneath this Santa outfit.

451
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,240
Your pyjamas.

452
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:31,200
You're too shy to wear
less than two layers.

453
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:33,200
You could have used your imagination.

454
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:35,400
Yeah, I don't really have to.

455
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,640
DOCTOR: Clara!

456
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:42,800
Clara, you're dreaming.

457
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:44,880
You're dying.

458
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:47,200
Can you hear me?

459
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:48,880
Clara?

460
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:51,560
We did try to waken the others.
No stimulus worked.

461
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,360
Okay, we kill it.

462
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:57,800
We find a way to kill it, and we get it
off of her. How do we kill it?

463
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:59,840
There's no way to kill it
without killing your friend, too.

464
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:02,280
And as a scientist, may I just say,
I don't like the way you're talking.

465
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:04,360
Santa, in the infirmary,

466
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:07,960
you told the sleepers to go to bed,
and they obeyed you.

467
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,840
Sorry, doesn't mean
I can get that creature off her.

468
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,720
No, but you could get back
in there, unharmed, right?

469
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,640
What? You're asking Santa for help.
He doesn't exist.

470
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:16,320
And how would you know that?

471
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:21,200
How did you become an expert
on what does, and doesn't exist?

472
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:28,600
I can commit several million
housebreaks in one night,

473
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,160
dressed in a red suit with jingle bells.

474
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,880
So of course I can get back
into the infirmary.

475
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,320
Good.

476
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:36,560
Because there is only one way
that I can communicate with Clara.

477
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:40,840
(LOW RUMBLING)

478
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,760
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

479
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,520
-Your dad?
-(KNOCKING RESUMES)

480
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:02,440
Going by the timing, I'd say so.

481
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,680
Hmm.

482
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:05,440
If you let him anywhere
near the subject of golf,

483
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,960
I will do a thing,
and it will not be a good thing.

484
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:10,680
Um... Aren't we giving him golf clubs?

485
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:12,960
And I'm prepared to use them.

486
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:15,200
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

487
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:19,000
(SIGHING)

488
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,080
Hi.

489
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,360
Hi.

490
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:29,680
Doctor?

491
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,760
It's not real, Clara.

492
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:33,440
You know it's not real.

493
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:36,040
It's a dream. And it's killing you.

494
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:40,480
Merry Christmas.

495
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,360
You remember Danny, of course.

496
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:45,680
Not as well as you, clearly.

497
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,360
You've made him a fraction taller.
Merry Christmas, PE.

498
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:48,840
Compliments of the season, sir.

499
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:51,760
Dialogue's pretty good, too.
Nice work. It's all in the detail.

500
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,200
Just stop it.

501
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,760
He's not real, Clara.

502
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:57,800
None of this is real.

503
00:28:58,280 --> 00:29:01,120
What's real is,
there is an alien organism

504
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,600
wrapped around your face,

505
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:05,600
keeping you warm and happy
while it eats you.

506
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:07,400
Mince pie, anyone?

507
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:09,440
You're dying.

508
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:12,240
If this is a dream, how can you be here?

509
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:14,440
How can we both
be having the same dream?

510
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:15,840
There was only one way to get to you.

511
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,600
-And what was that?
-I'm dying, too.

512
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:20,760
(LOW RUMBLING)

513
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:30,400
Have we just killed him?
Have we just made it worse?

514
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:33,240
He thinks he can join the dream,
get her out.

515
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,440
Have a little faith.

516
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,400
You just wake up.
Just leave me here, please.

517
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,840
You have a pain right here.

518
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:47,040
It's like an ice cream pain, but gentle.

519
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:48,560
Do you know what that is?

520
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:52,760
The skin and bone have been parted
probably half an inch,

521
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:55,200
and something has pushed
right into the soft tissue of your brain

522
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:56,640
and is very slowly dissolving it.

523
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:58,720
I want you to picture it this way...

524
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:01,840
Somebody has put a straw
right through your skull

525
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:04,600
and is drinking you.
You should be screaming

526
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:06,880
with agony, but there's an aesthetic.

527
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:09,280
Everything around you right now,

528
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:12,520
even Danny, especially Danny,
that's the an aesthetic.

529
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:14,400
Why are you doing this?
Why are you saying all of that?

530
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:17,120
Because it's true.
How long do you think you've been here?

531
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:21,080
-All day.
-No, no, no, no.

532
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:24,280
Barely five minutes.
Because dream time goes faster.

533
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:25,920
Because this isn't real.

534
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:28,120
Danny isn't real.

535
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:33,240
Danny Pink died saving the world.

536
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:34,560
I really didn't.

537
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,600
DOCTOR: I'm sorry. I thought
there was a way back for him,

538
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,760
but I was wrong,
I can't change that, he's dead.

539
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:44,200
I didn't die saving the world, Doctor,
I died saving Clara.

540
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:46,560
The rest of you just got lucky.

541
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:51,080
How long has she got?

542
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:55,880
Minutes, till it's irreversible.

543
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,680
Well, then get out the way.

544
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:05,480
I'm a dream and you know I am. Right?

545
00:31:09,280 --> 00:31:10,680
Now, one thing.

546
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:14,800
But it's important.
It's a very important thing.

547
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:17,000
That is totally how you
guessed all my presents.

548
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:18,720
(LAUGHS)

549
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:27,080
-I miss you.
-DANNY: Five minutes.

550
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:30,560
-What?
-You can miss me for five minutes a day.

551
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,560
And you better do it properly,

552
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:35,200
you better be sad, I expect my five.

553
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:38,560
But all the rest of the time, Clara,

554
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:41,400
all the rest of the time,
every single second,

555
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:43,280
you just get the hell on with it.

556
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,400
Clear?

557
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:49,080
-Don't you soldier me.
-Do as you're told.

558
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:52,160
-Brave.
-Dead already.

559
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,680
-How does she wake up?
-DOCTOR: I don't know.

560
00:31:58,320 --> 00:32:01,800
Just try.
Accept this isn't real and try.

561
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,720
DANNY: Do it, for me.

562
00:32:08,040 --> 00:32:09,560
(SNIFFLING)

563
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,520
When I wake up, you won't be there.

564
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:18,120
DANNY: Do you know why people
get together at Christmas?

565
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:21,920
Because every time they do,
it might be the last time.

566
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:25,840
Every Christmas is last Christmas.
And this is ours.

567
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:29,760
This was a bonus. This is extra.

568
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,000
But now it's time to wake up.

569
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,560
(SCREAMS)

570
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:47,440
(GASPS)

571
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:48,640
-(COUGHS)
-Clara?

572
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:51,800
Clara, Clara, look at me.
Clara, Clara, breathe!

573
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:54,120
Breathe, breathe, breathe.

574
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:05,440
(LOW WHIRRING)

575
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,360
So these creatures,
when their feeding goes wrong, they die.

576
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:16,760
The carnivore's hazard,
food has teeth, too.

577
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,400
-Are you okay?
-No.

578
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:25,880
Good. There are some things
we should never be okay about.

579
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:31,920
-There doesn't seem to be a wound.
-No.

580
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,720
And the pain's still there, isn't it?

581
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:36,440
Is it the ice cream pain? Just here?

582
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:38,720
-'Cause I've got that.
-It's the cold, I think.

583
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:40,440
Some sort of reaction.

584
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:42,160
But only on one side,
just that spot there.

585
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,760
Doesn't that strike you as odd?

586
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:45,320
Well, we've all got it.

587
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:47,320
Okay. So why do we all have that pain?

588
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:49,440
-Theorise.
-Don't treat me like a beginner.

589
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:53,920
I was dreaming,
then I woke up, I know that.

590
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:57,800
Do you?
And have you ever woken up from a dream

591
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:59,280
and discovered that
you're still dreaming?

592
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:05,080
Dreams within dreams,
dream states nested inside each other.

593
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:06,200
All perfectly possible.

594
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:09,000
Especially when we're dealing with
creatures who have weaponised

595
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:10,800
our dreams against us.

596
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:13,800
Well, I don't know about anybody else,

597
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:16,280
but I'm pretty certain
I'm awake right now.

598
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:18,880
Which is odd, when you think about it.

599
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:22,280
-0dd?
-Impossible, in fact.

600
00:34:23,280 --> 00:34:24,680
How can any of us be awake?

601
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,000
I don't understand.

602
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:30,400
Remember how we all first met?
In the infirmary?

603
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,320
Come on, quick, quick, quick, come on.

604
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,600
Go, run, now!

605
00:34:34,080 --> 00:34:36,360
All those creatures coming down
from the ceiling, attacking us.

606
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,840
Here they come!

607
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:38,960
(ALL SCREAMING)

608
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,520
DOCTOR: We never stood a chance.

609
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,800
How did we survive that?

610
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:47,240
Well, we... We were rescued.

611
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,440
Yeah, we were rescued.

612
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:54,080
And who was it that rescued us?

613
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:58,400
No, no, no, no. I need you to do
the east coast right now.

614
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,640
Well, otherwise
we're gonna be delivering

615
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:03,280
to the islands in broad daylight. Yeah.

616
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,840
Listen, please try and remember
that our mug shots

617
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:08,080
are on every Christmas card.

618
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:11,920
Yeah, just get it done,
head toward the northern lights.

619
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,760
Yes, I remembered to switch them on.

620
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:16,200
The Helman-Ziegler test,

621
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:18,560
the only reliable dream test
that I know.

622
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:23,480
Your base manual. I take it that
none of you have memorised this.

623
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:24,880
Oh, erm... I haven't read it.

624
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:28,120
These books should be
identical in the real world.

625
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:31,920
But as they don't exist in your memory,
in a dream, they can't be. Agreed?

626
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:37,360
Clara, give me any two-digit number.

627
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,800
-Fifty-seven.
-All right.

628
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,720
All of you, turn to page 57.

629
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,440
And look at the very first word.

630
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,200
Right, when I point at you...

631
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:50,320
"Isotope.”

632
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:55,680
-Well?
-"Extremely."

633
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:58,600
"Inside."

634
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:03,080
"Chocolate.” Why did I get
"chocolate"? What's that about?

635
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:05,640
This can't be right.
We must have got it wrong, that's all.

636
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:07,160
Well, we'll do it again. Clara.

637
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:08,760
-Twenty-four.
-Twenty-four.

638
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:13,400
-"We_"
-"Are."

639
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,400
"ALL"

640
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,040
Shona?

641
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:23,440
"Dead."

642
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:30,800
Since the attack in the infirmary,
nothing has been real?

643
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:34,080
The attack is still going on.
This is it.

644
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:36,120
We've been dreaming since then?

645
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:38,520
SANTA: Oh, for Easter's sake!

646
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:41,520
Of course you've been dreaming.

647
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:44,240
Haven't you been paying attention?

648
00:36:45,680 --> 00:36:48,280
Rudolph. Did you see the nose?

649
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,960
The North Pole? Come on, with stripes?

650
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:54,400
-This...

651
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:56,480
ALL: ...a dream.

652
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:59,800
SANTA: How much more obvious
do you want me to make it?

653
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,640
Because I can text
the Easter Bunny, you know.

654
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:04,400
Seriously? You're trying to help?

655
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,840
As you stand here, chatting,

656
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:11,280
chatting, your lives are ending.

657
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:14,760
Unless you wake up,
unless you free yourselves

658
00:37:14,840 --> 00:37:18,200
from these dreadful creatures,
they're gonna destroy you.

659
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:19,960
You're a dream who's trying to save us?

660
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:23,840
Shona, sweetheart, I'm Santa Claus.

661
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,040
I think you just defined me.

662
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:29,320
This makes perfect sense.

663
00:37:30,480 --> 00:37:33,000
The dream crab tries to make the dream

664
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:35,840
as real as possible to trap you inside.

665
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:38,800
It creates dreams within dreams

666
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:41,240
SO you can never be sure
if you are really awake.

667
00:37:41,640 --> 00:37:43,880
But your brain knows something is wrong,

668
00:37:45,160 --> 00:37:46,520
your subconscious fights back.

669
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:50,520
This is your mind trying to tell you
that this isn't real.

670
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:53,200
And so it gives you me.

671
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:54,800
Sweet Papa Crimbo!

672
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:58,480
It gives you comedy elves,
flying reindeer.

673
00:37:58,760 --> 00:38:01,080
-Exactly.
-A time travelling scientist

674
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:02,520
dressed as a magician.

675
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:03,920
(LAUGHS) Classic!

676
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:06,080
No, no, no. Hang on, no, no, no, no!

677
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,720
Living in a phone box.

678
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:10,120
It's a spaceship in disguise.

679
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,600
You see how none of this
makes any sense.

680
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:15,360
Shut up, Santa.

681
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:18,280
I've watched over you all your lives.

682
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:21,360
I've taken care of you
from Christmas to Christmas.

683
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:22,880
But you're not real.

684
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:26,040
And yet that never stopped me.

685
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:29,160
All of you, come here.
Come here, come on. Join hands.

686
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:31,920
No, no, look, we don't need
all this touchy-feely stuff...

687
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,480
Shut up, Doctor.

688
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:35,440
Join hands, come on, concentrate.

689
00:38:35,720 --> 00:38:36,800
Why?

690
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:39,280
You're deep inside
this dream, all right?

691
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:40,800
And it is a shared mental state,

692
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:44,360
so it's drawing power from
the multi-consciousness gestalt

693
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:45,760
which has now formed telepathically...

694
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:48,160
No, no. No, no, no. Line in the sand.

695
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:51,040
Santa Claus does not do
the scientific explanation.

696
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:52,720
All right, as the Doctor might say,

697
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:54,840
"Oh, it's all a bit dreamy-we a my."

698
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,760
Why don't you just go
and make a naughty list?

699
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:58,280
I have, mate, and you're on it.

700
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:59,720
Don't give me that look,
you're supposed to be warm

701
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:00,880
and friendly and cheerful.

702
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:02,960
Oh, yeah, look at your great
bedside manner.

703
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:05,600
-Don't be so hostile.
-Doctor, behave.

704
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,520
This is very sweet,

705
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:11,400
but right now I have an alien life form
wrapped around my face,

706
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:13,120
and apparently it's digesting my brain.

707
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,040
When you speak,

708
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:17,360
how do I know it's not the dream crab?

709
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:20,440
Oh, good question.
Spoken like a scientist.

710
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:22,600
CLARA: Can I put it another way?

711
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:26,280
Why would the part of our brain
that is trying to keep all of us alive,

712
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:28,320
choose you for a face?

713
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:32,760
-Is anyone else asking that?
-Yeah, yeah, yeah. All of us.

714
00:39:33,320 --> 00:39:34,800
All of us. Why you?

715
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:38,840
Why me?

716
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:42,400
It's the North Pole. It's Christmas Day.

717
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:44,640
And you're dying.

718
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:46,240
Who are you gonna call?

719
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:49,080
Just one last time, huh?

720
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:53,120
One last Christmas,
as if your lives depended on it.

721
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:54,400
Please!

722
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:58,040
Ho-ho-ho! Believe in Santa.

723
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,360
-I'm not very good with this...
-CLARA: Tough!

724
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:03,760
...holdy-hand thing.

725
00:40:03,840 --> 00:40:05,440
I will hold Clara's hand, but that's...

726
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:07,880
-Shona, take his hand.
-No, no, I'm fine, I'm fine.

727
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:09,880
This is very Christmassy, isn't it?

728
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:12,400
Okay, so what do we...

729
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,080
BELLOWS: Where did he go?

730
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,200
We're waking up.

731
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,880
That part of the dream is over,
we're on our own Now.

732
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,720
Well then, what do we do?

733
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,840
That pain in your head, make it worse.

734
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:26,680
Head towards it.

735
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:28,600
So when we wake up, what do we expect?

736
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:30,880
Only a few moments
will have passed at the most.

737
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,240
The attack is still in progress.

738
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,400
I'm scared.

739
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,760
Congratulations, that means
you're not an idiot.

740
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:38,240
It's not like the last time.

741
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:39,480
Last time wasn't real.

742
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:42,600
Good luck. Stay calm.

743
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:47,120
And God bless us, everyone.

744
00:40:56,720 --> 00:40:58,040
(ALL GASPING)

745
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,000
Run!

746
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:09,840
-CLARA: No!
-Clara!

747
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,480
Doctor!

748
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:13,760
(GRUNTING)

749
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:17,640
ASHLEY: Out! Out!

750
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:19,000
Now, now!

751
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:23,840
(WHIMPERS)

752
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:29,840
-Everyone all right?
-Yeah.

753
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:32,280
Good. Bye.

754
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:35,600
Sorry, I'll just go and...

755
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:38,440
No need for chatting,
you'll only get attached.

756
00:41:38,520 --> 00:41:39,880
This isn't Facebook.

757
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:44,800
Uh, what about the dream crabs?

758
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:46,160
Oh, they're fine.

759
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:49,920
-And the people that they're eating.
-Beyond help.

760
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,960
Doctor, the others are still in danger.

761
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,400
Only if they're stupid.

762
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,520
There are polar bears on this ice cap,

763
00:41:56,600 --> 00:41:58,520
am I supposed to do
something about that, too?

764
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:00,680
We know dream crabs are still on Earth.

765
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:02,120
There are lots of dangerous things

766
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:05,280
on this funny little planet of yours,
Clara, most of which you eat.

767
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:07,000
I'm a doctor, not your Mam.

768
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:11,120
Doctor.

769
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:14,960
If Santa was only in the dream,

770
00:42:16,160 --> 00:42:18,040
why was he on my roof?

771
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:24,640
Four... Four patients.

772
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:27,560
Four manuals.

773
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:29,040
Hurry!

774
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:32,760
Do you know what I hate
about the obvious?

775
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:35,400
-What?
-Missing it!

776
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:42,480
As you were, don't salute.

777
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:44,960
Are you the same people as before?

778
00:42:45,280 --> 00:42:47,280
-Of course they are.
-Oh, I'm sorry, I deleted you.

779
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,240
Well, that's not
a very nice attitude, is it?

780
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:53,120
-Four manuals, yes?
-Yes, why?

781
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:55,120
-One each.
-One each, yes.

782
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:57,120
-What's the problem?
-Well, the problem is,

783
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:58,520
you can't see the problem.

784
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:00,680
For instance, you, gobby one.

785
00:43:01,480 --> 00:43:03,840
-I have a name, actually.
-Doesn't matter, I don't need it.

786
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:06,400
When we first met you
in the infirmary, what were you doing?

787
00:43:06,800 --> 00:43:08,960
Hmm, it's a long story.

788
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:12,840
Uptight boss one, what is
the primary mission of this polar base?

789
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:15,000
-It's a long story.
-Sexy one.

790
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:18,160
What brings you
to the North Pole at your age?

791
00:43:18,520 --> 00:43:20,280
It's a long story.

792
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:22,600
Okay. Why are they all
giving the same answer?

793
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:23,920
Because that is a tiny bit freaky.

794
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:26,480
If you think that's freaky, try this.

795
00:43:26,560 --> 00:43:27,720
We were in the Tardis.

796
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:31,280
-Why did we come here?
-It's a long story.

797
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:37,280
-Doctor?
-Dreams...

798
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:40,080
They're funny. (LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY)

799
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:42,240
They're disjointed.

800
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:46,000
They're silly, they're full of gaps.

801
00:43:46,080 --> 00:43:48,600
But you don't notice,
because the dream protects itself.

802
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:51,360
Stops you asking the right questions.

803
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:54,920
For example, why do you have
four manuals, one each,

804
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,680
when you have a crew of eight?

805
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:01,160
Or did you forget about
your friends in the infirmary here?

806
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:04,440
But we woke up!

807
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:06,600
DOCTOR: Dreams within dreams,
I warned you.

808
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:08,640
No, this isn't a dream, I know it isn't.

809
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:10,640
No one knows they're not dreaming.

810
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:12,640
Not one of us, not ever.

811
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:15,400
Not for one single moment of our lives.

812
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:20,400
Clara, page number? Make it a good one.

813
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:23,240
Twelve.

814
00:44:26,200 --> 00:44:27,640
-"Very."
-"Very.

815
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:29,120
"Very."

816
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,120
"Dead."

817
00:44:32,400 --> 00:44:34,360
And who's going to be
the first to admit it?

818
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:36,440
-Admit what?
-That the pain is still there.

819
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:39,960
Actually, I think it's getting worse.

820
00:44:40,040 --> 00:44:43,000
DOCTOR: Yes, there is an alien organism
in your brain, eating it.

821
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,720
-Of course it's getting worse.
-Doctor.

822
00:44:46,120 --> 00:44:47,200
What are they doing?

823
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:50,680
Factually, getting up.

824
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:53,960
-Significantly, sensing the end game.
-How?

825
00:44:54,240 --> 00:44:55,320
I don't understand.

826
00:44:56,600 --> 00:44:57,960
Well, look at them. Go on.

827
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:01,960
Look at them. Look at them properly.
Look who they are.

828
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:07,040
They're you! The sleepers are you.

829
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:09,520
How can they be us?

830
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:11,800
DOCTOR: Because we're dreaming,
all of us.

831
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:13,320
This base isn't real.

832
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:16,840
None of us are actually
standing in the room.

833
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:18,760
I'm probably asleep in my Tardis.

834
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:20,080
Clara, you must be in bed.

835
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:22,960
God knows where the rest of you are!
Probably scattered all over the world.

836
00:45:23,040 --> 00:45:26,480
But wherever you are,
the dream crabs have got us.

837
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:30,480
And we are all being networked
into the same nightmare.

838
00:45:33,600 --> 00:45:36,160
-What are they doing?
-It's your subconscious again.

839
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:38,560
The sleepers represent
the part of your mind

840
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:40,760
that's already surrendered
to the attack.

841
00:45:41,200 --> 00:45:43,200
These are dream images
of what's coming to kill you.

842
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:46,000
That's me, that's actually me.

843
00:45:46,360 --> 00:45:48,560
No, it's a metaphorical construct

844
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:51,400
representing a psychic attack
within a shared dreamscape.

845
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:52,520
Do please keep up!

846
00:45:52,680 --> 00:45:53,760
But it's me.

847
00:45:54,480 --> 00:45:55,680
Don't get too close.

848
00:45:56,040 --> 00:45:58,880
-Why?
-Because this is a nightmare.

849
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:01,800
(SCREAMING)

850
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:07,240
DOCTOR: Look out,
they're coming through!

851
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:11,160
Out, outside, now!
Run, run, run, run! Run!

852
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:15,000
Run, run, go! Go! Run!

853
00:46:29,720 --> 00:46:31,120
We'll freeze to death out here.

854
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:33,000
But it's... It's just a dream!

855
00:46:33,720 --> 00:46:36,480
This dream just killed your friend.
Start taking it seriously.

856
00:46:36,560 --> 00:46:39,000
Where's Albert? Where's the professor?

857
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:41,480
He probably just woke up
somewhere in the real world, dead.

858
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:44,640
If we don't wake up now,
we'll do the same.

859
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:45,920
But how?

860
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:48,600
-I don't know.
-(LOUD THUD)

861
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:56,680
The Tardis, come on!

862
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:57,840
-Come on!
-CLARA: Doctor!

863
00:46:57,920 --> 00:46:59,360
It's not the real Tardis.

864
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:01,200
Well, let's hope that
I dreamed it really well then.

865
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:06,800
(SLEEPERS GROWLING)

866
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,360
CLARA: It's us!

867
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:10,840
Of course it's us, we're dreaming too!

868
00:47:12,200 --> 00:47:13,360
Oh, my God!

869
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:16,600
BELLOWS: How is that possible?

870
00:47:17,200 --> 00:47:18,840
How can there be so many?

871
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:20,360
The logic of a nightmare.

872
00:47:20,440 --> 00:47:22,520
(CHITTERING)

873
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:24,720
(HISSING)

874
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:27,880
(GRUNTS)

875
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:29,800
So tell us how to wake up.

876
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:33,960
'Cause you're always talking like
you're so clever, going on and on.

877
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:35,240
So tell us what to do!

878
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:36,760
We have to leave this place.

879
00:47:36,840 --> 00:47:38,480
SHONA: Leave it?
BELLOWS: How?

880
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:41,240
-Use your imagination.
-Excuse me?

881
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:42,800
DOCTOR: Dream yourselves home!

882
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:46,000
But how?

883
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:49,560
DOCTOR: Come on.
It's Christmas, the North Pole.

884
00:47:49,920 --> 00:47:51,440
Who are you gonna call?

885
00:47:51,640 --> 00:47:53,280
(SLEIGH BELLS JINGLING)

886
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:06,360
SANTA: Yeah! Whoo!

887
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:10,000
Whoa! Get in the sleigh.

888
00:48:14,440 --> 00:48:15,720
(CHITTERING)

889
00:48:17,360 --> 00:48:19,520
Fortunately, I know
all your home addresses.

890
00:48:19,720 --> 00:48:20,960
-Yeah!
-(GASPS)

891
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:34,600
What happens now?

892
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:38,040
SANTA: Yeah!
CLARA: This is us just waking up, right?

893
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:39,680
DOCTOR: Could be. Well, I hope so.

894
00:48:40,440 --> 00:48:42,200
-Waking up or...
-or?

895
00:48:42,280 --> 00:48:45,480
Just focus on this,
do you believe in Santa Claus?

896
00:48:48,640 --> 00:48:50,640
I've always believed in Santa Claus.

897
00:48:52,240 --> 00:48:54,360
But he looks a little different to me.

898
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:06,960
Look!

899
00:49:11,440 --> 00:49:14,640
Hey, do you want to take
the reins, Doctor?

900
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:18,000
You're a dream construct,

901
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:21,600
currently representing either
my recovering or expiring mind.

902
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:23,680
SANTA: Yes, but do you want a go?

903
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:26,160
Yeah, all right!

904
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:27,480
Whoa! Oh!

905
00:49:27,640 --> 00:49:29,160
BOTH: Whoa!

906
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:30,920
(EVERYONE WHOOPING)

907
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,520
Sorry! Sorry! Sorry!

908
00:49:33,600 --> 00:49:34,960
SANTA: Easy! This way.

909
00:49:35,960 --> 00:49:37,600
(DOCTOR LAUGHING)

910
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:41,480
Up a bit, nose up. There we go.

911
00:49:41,800 --> 00:49:44,640
Oh! Look at me, look. Look at me!

912
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:47,880
Whoo!

913
00:49:50,720 --> 00:49:53,160
(ALL SCREAMING)

914
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:56,960
-Whoo-hoo!
-(BELL TOLLING)

915
00:50:02,160 --> 00:50:03,440
Look at me.

916
00:50:04,480 --> 00:50:06,040
I'm riding a sleigh.

917
00:50:07,240 --> 00:50:08,680
I'm riding a sleigh!

918
00:50:12,360 --> 00:50:13,840
Yippie-yi-yay!

919
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:18,240
Whoo-hoo!

920
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:20,760
-Oh! Maybe you could...
-Dive in.

921
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:27,200
I work in a shop.

922
00:50:27,560 --> 00:50:28,680
I'm sorry?

923
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:33,080
I thought I was a scientist.
That's rubbish!

924
00:50:33,600 --> 00:50:35,240
Finally, something that makes sense.

925
00:50:35,640 --> 00:50:37,400
You're horrible, you!

926
00:50:37,600 --> 00:50:39,240
-Perfume.
-What?

927
00:50:39,840 --> 00:50:42,520
I'm an account manager. For perfume.

928
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:45,080
Does this mean we're waking up?

929
00:50:47,600 --> 00:50:50,360
Possibly. With any luck,

930
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:53,040
we'll all wake up
in our proper times and places.

931
00:50:53,440 --> 00:50:54,520
Proper times?

932
00:50:54,720 --> 00:50:57,160
Well, we could all be
from different time zones.

933
00:50:57,520 --> 00:51:00,520
Time travel is always
possible in dreams.

934
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:04,480
We might not know each other,
not any of us.

935
00:51:04,880 --> 00:51:06,800
No, possibly not.

936
00:51:07,760 --> 00:51:09,160
Well, you know what we should do?

937
00:51:09,720 --> 00:51:12,920
We should swap numbers,
we should have a reunion.

938
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:15,520
Bellows!

939
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:22,360
Gran! Dinner's ready.

940
00:51:23,400 --> 00:51:24,680
Yes, sorry, I must have dozed off.

941
00:51:37,960 --> 00:51:42,960
Um, now I'm pretty sure
I can remember my number,

942
00:51:43,040 --> 00:51:46,960
so you memorise it, then you text me,
we can go for a curry...

943
00:51:47,080 --> 00:51:49,400
The chances of you remembering
any of this are very slim.

944
00:51:49,640 --> 00:51:51,360
Well, don't say that.

945
00:51:51,440 --> 00:51:53,000
We'll remember, won't we, Ashley?

946
00:51:53,800 --> 00:51:54,880
Ashley?

947
00:51:55,560 --> 00:51:56,800
(GASPS)

948
00:52:00,200 --> 00:52:01,280
(SCREAMS)

949
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,400
Am I next? Is it me now?

950
00:52:08,880 --> 00:52:10,880
Shona, you're going home.

951
00:52:11,560 --> 00:52:14,680
-You're surviving.
-Do you wanna hang out sometime?

952
00:52:15,280 --> 00:52:17,280
-We can just hang out.
-Sure.

953
00:52:19,560 --> 00:52:21,320
Santa, can I stay a bit longer?

954
00:52:25,560 --> 00:52:26,720
(GASPS)

955
00:52:26,800 --> 00:52:28,040
(DREAM CRAB SHRIEKING)

956
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:33,680
Gross!

957
00:52:47,680 --> 00:52:48,800
(SIGHS)

958
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:17,040
It's a pity we have to wake up, really.

959
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:21,360
It's not really something
you do every day, is it?

960
00:53:22,080 --> 00:53:24,360
No, no! Strictly once a year!

961
00:53:26,520 --> 00:53:30,600
If we stay, we die, Clara.

962
00:53:35,160 --> 00:53:36,840
You're always such a downer, Doctor.

963
00:53:43,240 --> 00:53:44,360
(SHRIEKING)

964
00:53:44,440 --> 00:53:45,640
(COUGHING)

965
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:49,680
Clara!

966
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:57,680
You really should be
waking up too, Clara.

967
00:53:59,080 --> 00:54:01,200
-Just a little longer.
-Why?

968
00:54:09,680 --> 00:54:12,160
Every Christmas is last Christmas.

969
00:54:17,440 --> 00:54:18,720
SANTA: Yeah!

970
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:23,120
(WHOOSHING)

971
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:30,560
DOCTOR: Oh, Clara.

972
00:54:31,720 --> 00:54:34,360
Might have known
that you would be the one to sleep in.

973
00:54:34,960 --> 00:54:38,240
Okay, I tracked the psychic signal here

974
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:40,200
and I'm pretty sure that
I know how to do this lark.

975
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:42,960
One of the advantages
of actually being awake.

976
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:44,640
So you just hold still.

977
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:48,880
And I'm just going to zap
the neural centres...

978
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:55,120
Okay.

979
00:54:55,920 --> 00:54:57,160
(GRUNTS) There you go.

980
00:54:58,280 --> 00:54:59,880
The dream crabs must have
got to me first,

981
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:01,280
then found you in my memory.

982
00:55:01,760 --> 00:55:04,320
The others were collateral damage.

983
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:10,960
Well! Good to see you properly at last.
How long's it been?

984
00:55:11,960 --> 00:55:13,000
Clara?

985
00:55:14,640 --> 00:55:16,120
Oh, you know.

986
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:19,560
About 62 years.

987
00:55:23,440 --> 00:55:24,760
Doctor.

988
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:28,640
I have missed you very much.

989
00:55:29,560 --> 00:55:31,000
You stupid old man.

990
00:55:32,400 --> 00:55:33,840
(CHUCKLES)

991
00:55:35,960 --> 00:55:38,320
I've missed you too.

992
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:46,120
These are Christmas hats,
I've seen people use them.

993
00:55:46,200 --> 00:55:48,360
You put them on
and absolutely anything seems funny.

994
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:50,360
Oh, probably won't work on you.

995
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:52,600
-Probably not. Do you wanna try?
-Go on then.

996
00:55:58,680 --> 00:56:00,240
Can you really see no difference in me?

997
00:56:00,760 --> 00:56:03,680
Clara Oswald, you will
never look any different to me.

998
00:56:06,120 --> 00:56:07,880
-So how was it then?
-How was what?

999
00:56:09,360 --> 00:56:11,200
The 62 years that I missed.

1000
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:14,200
Oh, how was my life, you mean?

1001
00:56:14,800 --> 00:56:16,760
-Is there a Mr Clara?
-No.

1002
00:56:17,400 --> 00:56:18,800
But there were plenty of proposals.

1003
00:56:19,520 --> 00:56:21,920
-They all turned you down then?
-I turned them down!

1004
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:27,920
I travelled.

1005
00:56:28,440 --> 00:56:30,440
I tought in every country in Europe.

1006
00:56:31,240 --> 00:56:32,560
(GASPS) I learnt to fly a plane.

1007
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:42,280
-Regrets?
-Oh, hundreds.

1008
00:56:42,360 --> 00:56:44,000
(CHUCKLING)

1009
00:56:44,080 --> 00:56:45,920
I just wish there were time
for a few more.

1010
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:49,120
Yeah. They're always the best part.
Christmas cracker, we should do one.

1011
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:56,000
No one ever matched up to Danny, eh?

1012
00:56:58,360 --> 00:57:00,120
There was one other man.

1013
00:57:00,280 --> 00:57:01,920
But that would never have worked out.

1014
00:57:02,520 --> 00:57:03,680
Why not?

1015
00:57:04,560 --> 00:57:05,680
He was impossible.

1016
00:57:11,840 --> 00:57:13,680
We should do this every Christmas.

1017
00:57:14,280 --> 00:57:17,440
Because every Christmas
is last Christmas.

1018
00:57:27,240 --> 00:57:28,560
I'm sorry.

1019
00:57:30,840 --> 00:57:34,960
I was stupid, I should have
come back earlier. I wish that I had.

1020
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,400
SANTA: Do you, Doctor?

1021
00:57:39,280 --> 00:57:40,960
How much do you wish that?

1022
00:57:42,600 --> 00:57:43,720
No.

1023
00:57:45,320 --> 00:57:47,240
-I'm not still...
-Wakey-wakey!

1024
00:57:47,960 --> 00:57:49,160
(COUGHS)

1025
00:57:51,440 --> 00:57:52,720
Clara.

1026
00:57:58,360 --> 00:57:59,720
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

1027
00:58:04,760 --> 00:58:06,040
(GASPING)

1028
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:13,160
Doctor, am I young?

1029
00:58:13,440 --> 00:58:14,760
No idea.

1030
00:58:21,960 --> 00:58:24,600
-Is that any good?
-Oh, that's good.

1031
00:58:34,080 --> 00:58:35,840
The Tardis is outside.

1032
00:58:37,880 --> 00:58:39,000
So?

1033
00:58:39,560 --> 00:58:45,320
So all of time and all of space
is sitting out there in a big blue box.

1034
00:58:46,800 --> 00:58:49,560
Please, don't even argue.

1035
00:59:02,360 --> 00:59:04,320
Merry Christmas, Doctor.

1036
00:59:05,200 --> 00:59:07,480
Merry Christmas, Clara Oswald.

1037
00:59:09,520 --> 00:59:10,600
(CLARA CHUCKLES)

1038
00:59:14,440 --> 00:59:17,560
CLARA: Well, look at you, all happy.
(LAUGHS) That's rare.

1039
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:19,920
You know what's rarer? Second chances.

1040
00:59:20,520 --> 00:59:23,480
I never get a second chance,
so what happened this time?

1041
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:25,760
Don't even know who to thank.

1042
00:59:35,680 --> 00:59:37,400
(WHOOSHING)

1043
00:59:40,400 --> 00:59:42,720
(SLEIGH BELLS JINGLING)

